Titulo: A new composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with zirconia-based electrolytes

Sentencas: (LSM) and an ionic conductor Y- and Ce- co-doped Bi2O3 (BYC7).
Titulo: A new composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with zirconia-based electrolytes

Sentencas: BYC7 is an excellent oxide-ion conductor, exhibiting a high and stable ionic conductivity of 0.008 S cm(-1) at 500 degrees C.
Titulo: A new composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with zirconia-based electrolytes

Sentencas: The polarization resistance of LSM-BYC7 cathode in a symmetrical cell with doped ZrO2 as electrolyte varies from 5.76 at 500 degrees C to 0.25 Omega cm(2) at 650 degrees C.
Titulo: A new composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with zirconia-based electrolytes

Sentencas: The surface diffusion and charge transfer at the triple phase boundaries are the rate determining steps based on the dependence of polarization resistance on partial pressure of oxygen.

Sentencas: The maximum power density of a ZrO2-based anode-supported cell with LSM-BYC7 composite cathode is 56.4, 154.6, 327.9, and 451.0 mW cm(-2) at 500, 550, 600, and 650 degrees C respectively.
Titulo: A new composite cathode for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells with zirconia-based electrolytes

Sentencas: AC impedance analysis reveals that the performance of IT-SOFC prepared in this study is actually limited by the anode, not by LSM-BYC7 cathode.
